meta_feedback: You didn't ask about if we had 1 parent or not growing up. I have only ever had a mother, never a father in the picture. I tried to convey this in answers, but it was all clicking buttons. I may have answered the divorce question wrong, but they were never married so I didn't think of it initially. If you ever do this study again, I suggest setting up the answers first asking if the participant has a single parent household or not, which parent it is, and then continuing from there, so the data can include whether or not its 2 parent, single father, or single mother. These environmental factors play into whether or not for instance someone would get in a fight or not, even if they lived in a more dangerous or more safe neighborhood. The format of the "'at least one parent" sort of includes this but negligence from 2 whole parents vs 1 parent/1 not negligent vs only 1 parent vs only 1 negligent parent are differnt dynamics.
